title: March Madness continues: Live updates, highlights, results from round of 32
description: Follow along with the first day of the round of 32.
author: ESPN

title: Calipari back in Sweet 16 amid 'rewarding' season
description: John Calipari is heading to the Sweet 16 for the 16th time, guiding the Razorbacks past nemesis Rick Pitino and second-seeded St. John's 75-66 on Saturday to bring his fourth school to the NCAA tournament's second week.

title: England begin bid for legacy-defining year
description: England start their Women's Six Nations title defence against Italy, with this summer's legacy-defining home Rugby World Cup coming into view.

title: 'Mr Calm' Bellamy looks to Skopje after opening World Cup qualifying win
description: Wales captain Ben Davies says boss Craig Bellamy was "Mr Calm" after his side made hard work of their opening World Cup qualifier to beat Kazakhstan.

title: Hamilton hits out at 'yapping' critics for making 'uneducated guesses'
description: Lewis Hamilton has hit out at "yapping" critics for making "uneducated guesses" about his Ferrari debut struggles, after completing a remarkable turnaround to win the Chinese Grand Prix Sprint.

title: Hamilton claims China Sprint pole in lift-off for Ferrari career
description: Lewis Hamilton claimed a stunning pole for Saturday's Sprint at the Chinese Grand Prix in just his second race weekend with Ferrari.

title: Rockies trade OF Nolan Jones to the Guardians for INF/OF Tyler Freeman
description: The Colorado Rockies traded outfielder Nolan Jones to the Cleveland Guardians for Tyler Freeman on Saturday. The addition of Freeman provides increased flexibility for Colorado after it lost Thairo Estrada to a broken right wrist. The 25-year-old Freeman has made big league starts at second base, third, shortstop and center field.

title: Texas A&M gains commitment from elite 2026 4-star RB out of Cibolo (TX)
description: Texas A&M has gained its first running back commitment in the 2026 class, as four-star Jonathan Hatton chose the Aggies over Oklahoma on Saturday.
